reviewText:
A  NON-REVIEWER, REVIEW.
I got this game for free - however, from what I rember from when I last played the game (not the steam release) the game was pretty darn fun. Now that I'm looking at it, there's 2 things so far that have slightly annoyed me - the controls. To put it bluntly, at the moment, when playing with a 360 controller, it kind of feels like your wrestling with it, on default controlls. However, that is my opinion, but remapping some of the controllers makes it a lot easier to play through - especialy helping, for me, with not pressing attack, when I meant to jump - and doing so, having to restart a platforming section. Aside from that, the next and final issue I've found is that the subtitles look out of place, as in, they look almost fuzzy. To put it bluntly the game looks good, but then the subs look wrong - almost out of place.
EDIT: ONE MORE ISSUE;
The cutscenes. The cutscenes are jarring, in comparison to the rest of the game. In my opinion, they could recieve an update, however if you're not running this in 1920x1080, I can't comment on how they'd look. Despite this, the game is still over all pretty good. Though, it is only some - the consistensy on how the cutscenes/animations look isn't exactly there
EDIT:  ANOTHER ISSUE;
The lips don't sync up. Yep. That's it. It's kind of like you're watching a realy badly dubbed anime. You know,  it's translated, it's animated nicely, but you can't quite keep yourself looking at it. You can't quite get a true grasp of how the game looks, preforms and operates, it's jarring. It's a small, but extremley noticable things - to the point, one character wasn't talking, but their lips were moving (insert a joke about the Meghan Trainor song here)

Aside from that, the graphics look pretty good - a cutesy cell shaded graphics style, the voices fit, the music is excelent, comedic timing is pretty good - and a few of teh jokes directed at characters made me chuckle a fair bit, an  Intresting  combat system - over all, it's pretty good. I'd give it a 7/10. Not the best game, but considering it's old, and a port, it's not too shabby. The problems could be improved, and the in game dialogue regarding controller inputs could be changed based upon what it detects as per the game pad  (y being refered to in game as z, being the most noticable one). If you want to see as to whether or not this game is for you - just look at a lets player, mute the person playing if you want, but judge it from how it looks.

UPDATE 3;
I've put in another hour or so of gameplay. The game's style changes, it appears as though it was only the opening animation to the monster viliage" area of the game
